==Abstract==

This IIP defines the Lightning Network implementation for INTcoin, a second-layer payment protocol enabling instant, high-volume transactions. Adapted from Bitcoin BOLTs for ML-DSA-87 post-quantum signatures.

==Motivation==

On-chain INTcoin transactions have inherent limitations:
* Confirmation Time: 1-minute average blocks still require confirmations
* Throughput: Block size limits constrain volume
* Fees: On-chain fees prohibitive for micropayments
* Privacy: All transactions publicly visible

Lightning Network enables:
* Instant Payments: Sub-second confirmation
* High Throughput: Millions of transactions per second
* Low Fees: Minimal routing fees (<0.1 INT typical)
* Enhanced Privacy: Only channel opens/closes on-chain

==Specification==

===Terminology===

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Term !! Definition
|-
| INT || Base unit (1 INT = 10,000 base units)
|-
| Mint || Milli-INT for Lightning precision (1 INT = 10,000,000 mint)
|-
| Channel || Bidirectional payment channel
|-
| HTLC || Hash Time-Locked Contract
|}

===Post-Quantum Cryptography===

* Public Key Size: 2,592 bytes (ML-DSA-87)
* Signature Size: 4,627 bytes
* Security Level: NIST Level 5

===Channel Capacity Limits===

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Parameter !! Value
|-
| min_channel_size || 10 INT
|-
| max_channel_size || 1,000,000 INT
|-
| dust_limit || 0.0546 INT
|-
| channel_reserve || 1% of capacity
|-
| max_accepted_htlcs || 483
|}

===Fee Structure===

<pre>
fee = base_fee + (amount_mint * fee_rate_millionths / 1,000,000)
</pre>

Default: base_fee=1,000 mint (0.1 INT), fee_rate=1 (0.0001%)

===HTLC Limits===

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Parameter !! Value
|-
| min_htlc_mint || 1,000 (0.1 INT)
|-
| min_final_cltv_expiry || 40 blocks (~40 min)
|-
| max_cltv_expiry || 2,016 blocks (~2 weeks)
|}

